  "body": "NOTE: This is a placeholder issue as I haven't personally experienced this issue, please edit it/close it as appropriate.\r\n\r\n# Problem\r\n\r\nIt appears IPFS gateway is \"unreliable\" (NOTE: Unqualified statement, I don't know what people mean by this.)\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- Understand root cause of why unreliable\r\n- Fill upstream bug if necessary\r\n- Either fix or leave open as upstream or wontfix\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/8129#issuecomment-494431093%20question%20on%20TTT%20an\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/8129#issuecomment-494431093\r\n\r\n> for now to resume testing we need separate IPFS gateway, because given by Infura don't work all the times.\r\n\r\nSo I succeeded to install TTT <10 % cases (actually only two times during the whole day of testing) It is mentioned in 8 #8129 (comment).\r\n\r\nis this new behavior or have we obsreverd this a lot during testing last fwe months?\r\nis it specific to infura gateway? was a local node used during testing? is it a problem for a specific time? rate limited? what's the error response from gateway?\r\n\r\n> when I tested https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/7304 - I didn't notice this issue.\r\nThere I set up TTT a lot of times as well.\r\nso unless we changed a bunch of stuff, that seems to possibly point to a temporary infura overloaded issue\r\n\r\nso if we could isolate that behavior with specific response codes from gateway in a minimal example and show how it is non determinstic, we can point this to e.g. upstream and figure out root cause\r\nUpstream?\r\nhttps://github.com/INFURA/infura/issues/145\r\nhttps://discuss.ipfs.io/t/504-gateway-timeout/4995\r\nhttps://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/46638/how-long-does-infura-store-a-file-on-ipfs (old? re pinning)",
